gov.va.vinci.leo.descriptors

Class LeoTypeSystemDescription

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.va.vinci.leo.descriptors.LeoTypeSystemDescription

  • public class LeoTypeSystemDescription
extends Object
    Stores a type system description gov.va.vinci.leo.model that is used for import and creation of type objects.

    prafulla, Thomas Ginter

      • LeoTypeSystemDescription

        public LeoTypeSystemDescription(String descriptor,
                        boolean byName)
                         throws Exception
        Import the TypeSystemDescription from the descriptor provided either by name or by path.
        Parameters:
        descriptor - Path or name of the descriptor to be imported
        byName - If true then import the descriptor by name, otherwise import by the path provided.
        Throws:
        Exception - If the descriptor cannot be imported or the xml is invalid

      • LeoTypeSystemDescription

        public LeoTypeSystemDescription(String aType,
                        String aDescription,
                        String aSupertypeName)
        Create a new TypeSystem then add a type object with the name (aType), description, and name of the super type.
        Parameters:
        aType - Name of the initial Annotation Type initially being created
        aDescription - Description of the Annotation Type initially being created
        aSupertypeName - Name of the supertype from which this initial Annotation Type inherits

      • addType

        public LeoTypeSystemDescription addType(String aName,
                               String aDescription,
                               String aSuperType)
                                 throws Exception
        Add an Annotation Type to the TypeSystem with the name and supertype name provided. If a type with the same name already exist then the type will be ignored.
        Parameters:
        aName - Name of the Annotation Type to create and add.
        aDescription - Description of the Annotation Type that will be added
        aSuperType - Name of the Super Type that this Annotation Type will extend
        Returns:
        Reference pointer to this LeoTypeSystemDescription object, used in the builder pattern
        Throws:
        Exception - If either the name or the super type name are not provided

      • addType

        public LeoTypeSystemDescription addType(org.apache.uima.resource.metadata.TypeDescription aTypeDescription)
        Add an Annotation Type to the TypeSystem from the TypeDescription provided. If a type with the same name already exists then the type will not be added.
        Parameters:
        aTypeDescription - The type to be added
        Returns:
        Reference pointer to this LeoTypeSystemDescription object, used in the builder pattern

      • getType

        public org.apache.uima.resource.metadata.TypeDescription getType(String aTypeName)
        Return a TypeDescription object with the name provided. If that type is not found or there are no types in the TypeSystem then null is returned.
        Parameters:
        aTypeName - Name of the type to be found
        Returns:
        the TypeDescription or null if no such description is found

      • jCasGen

        public void jCasGen(String srcDirectory,
           String binDirectory)
             throws Exception
        Generate the .java files for the types in this TypeSystem then compile them into byte code to the bin directory specified.
        Parameters:
        srcDirectory - Path to the root source directory where the .java files will be generated, including package names
        binDirectory - Bin directory where .class files will be generated.
        Throws:
        Exception - If there is no type system or there is an error generating the .java files
